In order to access the data for the constant dimension case with parameters q;n;d andk, you query the URL http://subspacecodes.uni-bayreuth.de/api/ q/n/d/k/ 11

Similarly in the mixed dimension case, the URL is http://subspacecodes.uni-bayreuth.de/api/ q/n/d/ The result is a JSON ﬁle which contains a subset of the following attributes: request = contains your speciﬁed q;n;d andk  flower,uppergbound = lower or upper bound for the value Aq(n;d;k) comments = commentaries to this entry nondeduced = if the parameters are no parameters that are also viewable in the “short” mode, then they are trivial or computed using other parameters.

 flower,equal,uppergbound constraints = list of tuples which contain name, parameter and value of the applied constraints classiﬁed = boolean that is true if Aq(n;d;k)is classiﬁed up to isomorphism known codes = list of tuples of size, details, ﬁle (to enable automatic downloads) and nrisotypes (the number of isomorphism types of this entry) liftedmrdsizebound = the bound for codes that contains the lifted MRD code as described in Sub- section 3.2.3 In order to download the codes, you have to use the attribute ﬁle above and the URL http://subspacecodes.uni-bayreuth.de/codes/ ﬁle We want to remark that the API (as well as the whole homepage) is still in an evolutionary phase and therefore changes are may occur.
As an example, the the interested used may open the URL http://subspacecodes.uni-bayreuth.de/api/2/6/4/3/ .

David Mermin stated this point very clearly in http://arxiv.org/abs/1409.2454 : A very important dierence of QBism, not only from Copenhagen, but from virtually all other ways of looking at science, is the meaning of probability 1 (or 0).

QBism agrees with Wheeler that quantum measurements gives rise to new creation within the universe|he likened these creations to the big bang itself, see our http://arxiv.org/abs/1412.4209 |but QBism maybe even goes further than Wheeler would have, I don't know, in that it holds fast to this statement even when one has a p= 1 prediction beforehand.
